WEBVTT

00:01.543 --> 00:03.003
♪♪

00:03.003 --> 00:04.755
"What's up, Ryan?"

00:04.755 --> 00:05.714
What's up, JJ?

00:05.714 --> 00:09.676
♪♪

00:09.676 --> 00:10.719
Big finish...

00:10.719 --> 00:12.137
[ Grunts ]

00:12.137 --> 00:13.639
[ Imitates explosion ]

00:13.639 --> 00:16.808
♪♪

00:16.808 --> 00:17.851
Boogie.

00:19.645 --> 00:20.687
[ Imitates explosion ]

00:20.687 --> 00:25.609
♪♪

00:25.609 --> 00:27.569
Let's go fishing.

00:27.569 --> 00:29.446
It's a big one!

00:29.446 --> 00:30.614
[ Imitates explosion ]

00:33.575 --> 00:34.701
[ Scoffs ]

00:34.701 --> 00:35.536
I got this.

00:35.536 --> 00:39.122
♪♪

00:39.122 --> 00:40.582
I'm doing it!

00:40.582 --> 00:41.458
I'm cool!

00:44.753 --> 00:46.088
And now the fist bump.

00:46.088 --> 00:47.923
Unh!

00:47.923 --> 00:49.341
[ Imitates explosion ]

00:49.341 --> 00:50.551
[ Laughs ]

00:50.551 --> 00:52.594
Why do I always
have to blow out Ray's candle

00:52.594 --> 00:54.137
to make mine seem brighter?

00:55.055 --> 00:56.139
Eh.

01:00.435 --> 01:02.562
Ooh, Ray.

01:02.562 --> 01:04.064
Ray, what do you think
about this?

01:06.608 --> 01:08.151
Uh...I think it's crazy

01:08.151 --> 01:09.653
to buy next year's
winter clothes now

01:09.653 --> 01:10.988
just because
they're on sale.

01:10.988 --> 01:13.407
No, the crazy people are
the ones paying full price.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.826
Now, what size do you think
you're gonna be in nine months?

01:15.826 --> 01:18.078
Women's medium?

01:18.078 --> 01:19.705
Haven't got quite enough
up top yet, but don't worry.

01:19.705 --> 01:20.998
I was a late bloomer, too.

01:20.998 --> 01:23.208
I'm going to look for pins
on the floor.

01:23.208 --> 01:24.918
Get me when it's over.
Relax.

01:24.918 --> 01:26.587
All we got to do after this is
get Dylan from her sleepover,

01:26.587 --> 01:27.713
Dad from the barbershop,

01:27.713 --> 01:29.214
and go to JJ's
sled hockey tournament.

01:29.214 --> 01:30.757
Why can't we do
anything for <i>me?</i>

01:30.757 --> 01:32.968
I'm always just dragged around
to everybody else's stuff.

01:32.968 --> 01:34.469
Oh, love. All right.

01:34.469 --> 01:37.639
Well, just for you,
tomorrow, let's go swimming.

01:37.639 --> 01:40.350
We're going swimming because
a physical therapist told you

01:40.350 --> 01:42.352
that it would help
with JJ's muscle tightness.

01:42.352 --> 01:43.895
Oh, you heard that.
Yeah.

01:43.895 --> 01:46.231
Okay, you don't think
I like my Ray time.

01:46.231 --> 01:49.026
I would love to find something
for just you and me,

01:49.026 --> 01:50.694
but you disapprove
of my antics.

01:50.694 --> 01:52.321
All right, open or closed?
Closed.

01:53.655 --> 01:57.200
"That sled hockey game
sucked."

01:57.200 --> 01:59.244
"7‐0."

01:59.244 --> 02:00.579
Yeah, you guys
got to get better.

02:00.579 --> 02:02.331
It's hard to find things
to praise.

02:02.331 --> 02:04.124
Katie! Great game.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.292
Way to not throw up
on the ice.

02:05.292 --> 02:06.752
Oh, no, no,
I <i>did</i> throw up.

02:06.752 --> 02:08.754
I just kept it in my mouth
this time.

02:08.754 --> 02:10.130
Like a champion.

02:10.130 --> 02:13.300
<i>Anyway, you just look</i>
<i>at the board, and it speaks.</i>

02:13.300 --> 02:15.093
<i>You should ditch Kenneth</i>
<i>and get one.</i>

02:15.093 --> 02:16.803
Whoa! "Ditch Kenneth"?

02:16.803 --> 02:18.055
You taking shots now?

02:18.055 --> 02:19.348
Where was this
during the game?

02:19.348 --> 02:20.807
[ Laughs ]

02:20.807 --> 02:23.727
"I tried one years ago.

02:23.727 --> 02:25.729
I like this better."

02:25.729 --> 02:28.774
Yeah, he told me he likes
the independence a device gives,

02:28.774 --> 02:31.693
but for him, my human touch
makes for easier connections.

02:31.693 --> 02:33.528
<i>Can you watch porn</i>
<i>on Kenneth?</i>

02:33.528 --> 02:35.614
Porn?! You kiss your mother
with that board?

02:36.907 --> 02:39.493
Hey, guys! We were thinking
of seeing a movie Saturday.

02:39.493 --> 02:40.661
Who's in?

02:40.661 --> 02:41.787
Me!
I will!
<i>I'm in!</i>

02:41.787 --> 02:44.581
"Kenneth and I are in."

02:44.581 --> 02:46.750
Wait. We don't think
we should ask Kenneth first?

02:46.750 --> 02:47.626
I actually have plans.

02:48.919 --> 02:49.920
Dude, I have a date.

02:49.920 --> 02:52.506
[ Laughs ]
You don't believe me?

02:52.506 --> 02:54.257
<i>Does your date</i>
<i>look like this?</i>

02:55.467 --> 02:57.844
Oh! Nicholas!

02:57.844 --> 02:58.970
Parental controls!

02:58.970 --> 03:01.181
Maya: Right.
Grab your swimming trunks.

03:01.181 --> 03:02.015
Here we are.

03:02.015 --> 03:03.475
This is
a private club.

03:03.475 --> 03:05.060
Yeah, I looked
at some public pools.

03:05.060 --> 03:06.561
This just seemed nicer.

03:06.561 --> 03:08.689
We're not allowed here.
That's how it stays nicer.

03:08.689 --> 03:09.940
Ray, we're gonna sneak in.

03:09.940 --> 03:12.359
It's like you're trying
to make it extra not for me!

03:12.359 --> 03:14.778
Relax. It'll be easy.

03:14.778 --> 03:15.862
Jimmy:
It's 20 bucks for valet.

03:15.862 --> 03:17.030
Gah!

03:17.030 --> 03:18.407
There's
no wheelchair ramp.

03:18.407 --> 03:19.157
Gah!

03:19.157 --> 03:20.534
[ Door rattles ]

03:20.534 --> 03:21.910
That's locked.
Gah!

03:24.413 --> 03:26.832
[ Splash ]

03:26.832 --> 03:28.667
See? Too easy.

03:28.667 --> 03:30.669
Excuse me, love.

03:30.669 --> 03:32.629
Refill, please.

03:32.629 --> 03:36.508
Also, this little chap
no longer smells of lavender.

03:36.508 --> 03:38.176
Oh, God.
Somebody's coming over.

03:38.176 --> 03:40.887
Oh, darling, no, don't worry.
Just act like you belong.

03:40.887 --> 03:41.930
I don't know
how to do that

03:41.930 --> 03:43.598
at the places
I actually do belong!

03:43.598 --> 03:44.975
Uh‐oh. 5‐0.

03:44.975 --> 03:46.476
[ Both inhale deeply ]

03:46.476 --> 03:47.477
Hello.

03:47.477 --> 03:49.271
I'm sorry.
Are you members?

03:49.271 --> 03:51.022
Not here,
but we have privileges.

03:51.022 --> 03:52.649
We're at the Palms Club.

03:52.649 --> 03:53.859
I am not familiar
with that.

03:53.859 --> 03:55.527
Oh, it's in the UAE.

03:55.527 --> 03:57.654
I'd have you call them,
but it's 3:00 A. M. in Dubai,

03:57.654 --> 03:59.489
so...du‐bye!
[ Chuckles ]

04:02.492 --> 04:04.244
There you are. She left.
Now you can relax.

04:04.244 --> 04:05.662
Now I can relax?

04:05.662 --> 04:07.831
You might as well say
now I can do sports.

04:08.790 --> 04:11.001
Oh, my gosh!

04:11.001 --> 04:12.461
Hon, you got to tell us
when she leaves.

04:12.461 --> 04:14.171
Yeah, well, she's gone, darling.
Well done.

04:14.171 --> 04:16.673
♪♪

04:16.673 --> 04:18.842
Sir?
You'll need sandals.

04:18.842 --> 04:20.594
Thank you.
Our compliments.

04:20.594 --> 04:21.428
[ Thud ]

04:21.428 --> 04:22.721
Sir?

04:22.721 --> 04:23.805
Oh. That was st‐‐

04:23.805 --> 04:25.390
Strawberry.
We know, sir.

04:25.390 --> 04:26.808
Thanks.
Mm‐hmm.

04:26.808 --> 04:27.893
Could I get
an extra strawberry?

04:27.893 --> 04:29.728
Of course, sir.

04:29.728 --> 04:31.313
This is all for <i>you.</i>

04:32.689 --> 04:38.487
♪♪

04:38.487 --> 04:39.613
Thank you.

04:43.909 --> 04:45.744
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm home.

04:46.912 --> 04:49.289
Look, man, there's something
I want to discuss.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.373
It's been eating away
at me,

04:50.373 --> 04:52.876
and I need to have
my feelings heard.

04:52.876 --> 04:54.252
Wow, Ray.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.712
You look... different.

04:55.712 --> 04:57.589
[ Laughs ]

04:57.589 --> 04:59.883
Okay. Things like
what you did last night ‐‐

04:59.883 --> 05:02.219
signing me up for a movie
before you even asked ‐‐

05:02.219 --> 05:04.471
that makes me feel like
you take me for granted.

05:05.680 --> 05:07.557
"Oh. Okay.

05:07.557 --> 05:08.475
Oops."

05:08.475 --> 05:09.726
"Oops"?

05:09.726 --> 05:11.311
Huh. That feels nice.

05:11.311 --> 05:12.479
Thanks, JJ.

05:12.479 --> 05:14.773
I accept your "Oops."

05:14.773 --> 05:17.692
I'm just saying, I got a life
outside of here, man.

05:17.692 --> 05:22.447
"Well, I'm sorry if I'm getting
in the way of your life."

05:25.408 --> 05:28.495
"Well, I'm sorry if I'm getting
in the way of your life!"

05:28.495 --> 05:30.247
He said "more sassy."

05:30.247 --> 05:32.165
I‐I‐I get that you need me.
It's just ‐‐

05:32.165 --> 05:33.875
"Oh, I <i>need</i> you?"

05:33.875 --> 05:36.211
Oh, don't be that way. You know
that's not how I meant it.

05:36.211 --> 05:38.421
"I'm sorry
for being such a burden."

05:38.421 --> 05:39.464
Oh, here we go.

05:39.464 --> 05:42.509
"You know what?
Forget the movie."

05:42.509 --> 05:43.635
Wha‐‐

05:45.846 --> 05:47.848
Well, you don't have to
go home,

05:47.848 --> 05:49.766
but you can't stay here.

05:49.766 --> 05:54.604
♪♪

05:54.604 --> 05:56.439
Great. You're here.
We need to talk.

05:56.439 --> 05:58.567
We have a very busy week
coming up.

05:58.567 --> 06:00.235
There's a tennis clinic
tonight.

06:00.235 --> 06:03.029
Tomorrow, the dining room is
doing a Taste of Tuscany thing.

06:03.029 --> 06:04.531
Not gonna miss that.

06:04.531 --> 06:06.825
And Thursday,
they're doing an afternoon tea

06:06.825 --> 06:07.868
in the Botanical Gardens.

06:07.868 --> 06:10.245
Oh, I love afternoon tea.

06:10.245 --> 06:12.163
But I thought
you hated the club.

06:12.163 --> 06:14.541
I did hate it ‐‐
until I realized something.

06:14.541 --> 06:15.959
I love it.

06:15.959 --> 06:18.461
I've finally found
my people.

06:18.461 --> 06:22.007
I'm a fancy guy
trapped in a poor guy's body.

06:22.007 --> 06:24.134
I identify as rich!

06:24.134 --> 06:26.177
And is that
how you illustrate that?

06:26.177 --> 06:27.554
What's wrong
with my ensemble?

06:27.554 --> 06:28.722
Morning, everyone.

06:28.722 --> 06:29.973
Why are you wearing
your mother's pants?

06:29.973 --> 06:30.974
There's that.

06:30.974 --> 06:32.309
Forward‐point collar

06:32.309 --> 06:33.685
instead of
the preferred English spread.

06:33.685 --> 06:35.270
Visible undershirt.

06:35.270 --> 06:36.229
How do you know
that stuff?

06:36.229 --> 06:37.856
Darling, I'm British.

06:37.856 --> 06:39.858
We <i>invented</i>
sartorial nonsense.

06:39.858 --> 06:41.026
Could you teach me?

06:41.026 --> 06:42.444
At the club?

06:42.444 --> 06:43.737
Are you saying
there's something you'd enjoy

06:43.737 --> 06:45.947
that we could do
together?

06:45.947 --> 06:47.782
This could be
our thing...

06:47.782 --> 06:49.326
Mummy.

06:49.326 --> 06:53.872
Strike me down now, God,
for at last I am truly happy.

06:53.872 --> 06:55.915
I'd like to think
17 years of marriage

06:55.915 --> 06:58.168
loosened the lid
on that jar of happiness.

06:59.210 --> 07:00.879
Good morning, JJ.

07:00.879 --> 07:02.172
<i>Hello, Kenneth.</i>

07:03.381 --> 07:04.758
<i>What's the matter?</i>

07:04.758 --> 07:07.969
<i>Never seen a guy who didn't</i>
<i>need his aide before?</i>

07:09.888 --> 07:10.889
[ Imitates explosion ]

07:14.267 --> 07:15.685
So, what ‐‐ You went out
and got yourself

07:15.685 --> 07:18.521
a little talking computer dealie
just to get back at me?

07:18.521 --> 07:20.607
<i>My friend let me use</i>
<i>his old one.</i>

07:20.607 --> 07:21.941
<i>I like it.</i>

07:21.941 --> 07:24.944
<i>It's easy to work with</i>
<i>and doesn't eat my pizza.</i>

07:24.944 --> 07:27.614
Yeah, I'm sure you prefer
that robot over this voice.

07:27.614 --> 07:30.700
Mine is a freight train
dipped in smoked honey.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.410
The finest minds
in Silicon Valley

07:32.410 --> 07:35.455
could never make this
in their labs.

07:36.831 --> 07:39.167
[ Chime ]
<i>[ Deep voice ]</i>
<i>Well, I beg to differ.</i>

07:39.167 --> 07:41.336
[ Gasps ] That robot
could be my brother.

07:41.336 --> 07:43.630
[ Chime ]
<i>[ English accent ]</i>
<i>Checkmate, my good man.</i>

07:43.630 --> 07:45.507
Everyone's getting so British,
aren't they?

07:45.507 --> 07:47.717
[ Chime ]
<i>[ Sexy female voice ]</i>
<i>Can I have more cereal, Dad?</i>

07:47.717 --> 07:50.345
Oh, change it back!
That's very upsetting.

07:50.345 --> 07:53.014
Oh, so, you're no longer
interested in the human touch

07:53.014 --> 07:54.516
that this voice provides?

07:54.516 --> 07:56.059
No biggie. I got
plenty of things to read.

07:56.059 --> 07:57.602
Uh...

07:57.602 --> 08:00.230
"Great new taste."

08:00.230 --> 08:03.483
"Sex party probe widens."

08:03.483 --> 08:04.901
So, after school,
you're gonna pick me up

08:04.901 --> 08:06.069
and we're gonna
head over to the club?

08:06.069 --> 08:07.070
Sure thing.

08:08.613 --> 08:10.490
Oh, isn't that nice?

08:10.490 --> 08:14.035
Normally, all I hear from Ray
is what I'm doing wrong,

08:14.035 --> 08:15.912
and now
he wants me around.

08:15.912 --> 08:17.497
We're connected.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.749
<i>[ Audience "Aws" ]</i>

08:19.749 --> 08:21.000
That thing does
sound effects?

08:21.000 --> 08:22.502
<i>[ Laughter,</i>
<i>cheers and applause ]</i>

08:22.502 --> 08:27.173
♪♪

08:27.173 --> 08:29.008
Okay.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.677
Before we embark
on this adventure together,

08:30.677 --> 08:32.345
a few tips.

08:32.345 --> 08:34.347
First of all, no matter
what they present you with,

08:34.347 --> 08:36.516
you cannot appear
impressed.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.768
In fact, we better get
all of our gratitude

08:38.768 --> 08:40.687
and enthusiasm out now,
okay?

08:40.687 --> 08:41.521
One, two...

08:41.521 --> 08:43.690
Look at the thread count
on these napkins!
Oh, my God,
this is fantastic!

08:43.690 --> 08:45.984
This hot tub is bigger
than my bedroom!
Have you ever seen
so much shrimp?

08:45.984 --> 08:48.570
I can't believe
I'm meeting actual royalty!
This robe feels like
it's made out of baby skin.

08:48.570 --> 08:51.448
A room just for coats?!
Blimey! There's free mouthwash
in the loo!

08:51.448 --> 08:52.323
[ Both sigh ]

08:52.323 --> 08:54.117
Better, Ray?
Yeah.
Yeah.

08:54.117 --> 08:55.660
Maya:
<i>I know these people, Ray.</i>

08:55.660 --> 08:57.579
Pineapple‐kiwi water?
Fine.

08:57.579 --> 08:59.622
<i>You've got to build a persona.</i>
<i>Tell the big lie.</i>

08:59.622 --> 09:00.874
Steady.

09:00.874 --> 09:02.417
<i>And if you're ever in a corner,</i>

09:02.417 --> 09:04.586
<i>just tell them</i>
<i>you'd "rather not say."</i>

09:04.586 --> 09:07.881
So after our third safari,
we decided to settle down.

09:07.881 --> 09:09.591
As much as you can call
yacht life settling.

09:09.591 --> 09:10.592
[ Both laugh ]

09:10.592 --> 09:12.010
Where do you dock?

09:12.010 --> 09:13.303
I'd rather not say.

09:13.303 --> 09:14.471
[ Gasps ]

09:14.471 --> 09:16.181
<i>Anytime</i>
<i>you're in a conversation,</i>

09:16.181 --> 09:17.474
<i>make sure to be looking around</i>

09:17.474 --> 09:18.767
<i>for someone more important</i>
<i>to talk to.</i>

09:18.767 --> 09:20.643
What's your, uh, name?

09:20.643 --> 09:21.978
I'm, uh...

09:21.978 --> 09:23.813
What's that? Sorry?
Ray.

09:25.148 --> 09:26.524
[ Chuckles lightly ]

09:26.524 --> 09:28.485
I think we have a lot
to talk about, Ray.

09:28.485 --> 09:32.155
<i>Just follow me. I'll teach you</i>
<i>everything you need to know.</i>

09:32.155 --> 09:33.948
You've led enough.
Allow me.

09:36.159 --> 09:38.078
[ Waltz plays ]

09:38.078 --> 09:39.662
I watched a YouTube video.

09:39.662 --> 09:40.622
Did you?

09:48.463 --> 09:49.255
Dip?

09:49.255 --> 09:50.215
Please.

09:51.341 --> 09:53.259
[ Crowd "Aws," applause ]

09:55.637 --> 09:58.848
We danced, we laughed.
We had a breakthrough, Jimmy!

09:58.848 --> 10:01.017
Ray enjoyed
doing something with me.

10:01.017 --> 10:02.769
It's awesome ‐‐

10:02.769 --> 10:05.772
the facilities, the activities,
the hand towels.

10:05.772 --> 10:06.940
Just be aware,

10:06.940 --> 10:08.566
your mom is having
the time of her life, too.

10:08.566 --> 10:11.945
But the thing she is
most excited about...is <i>you.</i>

10:11.945 --> 10:13.404
How could she not be?

10:13.404 --> 10:14.781
Smell me!

10:14.781 --> 10:16.449
I am so well‐lotioned.

10:16.449 --> 10:18.576
They let you slather on
as much as you want.

10:18.576 --> 10:20.912
It is too much.
I can't hold anything.

10:20.912 --> 10:22.038
See?

10:22.038 --> 10:23.581
[ School bell rings ]

10:23.581 --> 10:27.293
[ Laughing ]

10:27.293 --> 10:28.461
Oh...

10:28.461 --> 10:30.463
Rudy Smith just made
a hilarious face.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.132
[ Chuckles ]

10:32.132 --> 10:33.967
But pointing out
hilarious faces to you

10:33.967 --> 10:36.594
is a service
I no longer provide.

10:36.594 --> 10:39.430
But since I like my job,
I'll keep doing it ‐‐

10:39.430 --> 10:41.349
for someone
who appreciates me.

10:41.349 --> 10:43.309
Now, I don't have
another nonverbal kid handy,

10:43.309 --> 10:46.604
but I do have Mary,
the super‐quiet kid.

10:46.604 --> 10:49.065
Yeah, I'll be
speaking for <i>her</i> today.

10:49.065 --> 10:51.276
Isn't that right, Mary?

10:51.276 --> 10:53.319
[ Mumbling softly ]

10:53.319 --> 10:54.821
Wait, wait ‐‐ What?
Speak up, Quiet.

10:54.821 --> 10:56.406
[ Mumbling louder ]

10:56.406 --> 10:59.826
Oh! [ Laughs ]

10:59.826 --> 11:02.996
You sure do have
a wicked sense of humor, Quiet.

11:02.996 --> 11:04.831
We're gonna get along
just fine.

11:06.457 --> 11:07.667
Just fine.

11:08.918 --> 11:10.628
Ray, I got you something.

11:12.922 --> 11:14.215
Tennis whites?!

11:14.215 --> 11:15.925
In‐season, full price?!

11:15.925 --> 11:17.260
Men's?

11:17.260 --> 11:19.304
I want my partner
looking his best

11:19.304 --> 11:21.264
in the mother/son
tennis tournament.

11:21.264 --> 11:23.099
Are you in?
Uh, yeah!

11:23.099 --> 11:24.559
[ Whispering ]
Acting impressed, Ray.

11:24.559 --> 11:26.686
Trying not to!
Can't stop!

11:26.686 --> 11:27.896
Spence: Hey, Ray.

11:27.896 --> 11:29.189
Hey, Spence.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.607
Let me introduce you
to my parents.

11:30.607 --> 11:33.067
My dad is a professor
of astronomy at CalTech.

11:33.067 --> 11:35.153
Mom is head of membership
at the club.

11:35.153 --> 11:38.072
I can... take those things
in stride.

11:38.072 --> 11:40.116
I'm Maya, Ray's mom.

11:40.116 --> 11:41.910
Of all the weeks
to visit the club.

11:41.910 --> 11:43.703
We're mid‐renovation.
Please forgive us.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.121
I'm sorry. I cannot.

11:47.040 --> 11:49.042
[ Laughing ] Oh!

11:49.042 --> 11:50.084
Enjoy your tea.
Mm.

11:52.712 --> 11:54.214
[ Whispering ]
Ehhhhhh!

11:54.214 --> 11:56.007
[ Whispering ]
What are you doing?!

11:56.007 --> 11:57.133
Retching.
Was it not clear?

11:57.133 --> 11:58.301
[ Imitates retching ]

11:58.301 --> 11:59.344
Really dull.

11:59.344 --> 12:01.095
Those are
the exact kind of people

12:01.095 --> 12:02.388
we need to be
getting to know.

12:02.388 --> 12:03.473
Why?

12:03.473 --> 12:05.725
We're not actually
part of this, Ray.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.894
You do realize that,
right?

12:07.894 --> 12:09.354
I'd rather not say.

12:09.354 --> 12:12.607
♪♪

12:12.607 --> 12:15.318
<i>I am going to say hi</i>
<i>to my friends.</i>

12:15.318 --> 12:18.488
<i>You can wait for me</i>
<i>in homeroom.</i>

12:18.488 --> 12:20.406
Really? You don't need me around
for the handshake?

12:20.406 --> 12:21.824
<i>I got it covered.</i>

12:23.159 --> 12:26.412
♪♪

12:26.412 --> 12:28.206
<i>Abort. Abort.</i>

12:28.206 --> 12:31.876
♪♪

12:31.876 --> 12:33.836
Wait. I got this.

12:33.836 --> 12:36.172
This is the <i>one</i> part of my day
I look forward to.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.425
♪♪

12:42.011 --> 12:44.264
What the heck,
Mr. Sharp?!

12:46.641 --> 12:50.353
[ Cellphone rings ]

12:50.353 --> 12:51.229
Hello?

12:51.229 --> 12:52.939
Ray, it's Spence.

12:52.939 --> 12:54.357
<i>From the club?</i>

12:54.357 --> 12:55.984
Oh. Spence.

12:55.984 --> 12:58.695
Sorry. I thought
you were Spence...

12:58.695 --> 12:59.946
my driver.

12:59.946 --> 13:01.698
Listen, a favor to ask ‐‐

13:01.698 --> 13:03.032
<i>for my mom.</i>

13:04.701 --> 13:06.995
Mom?
Ooh!

13:06.995 --> 13:09.706
I made cucumber sandwiches
like at the club.

13:12.417 --> 13:14.961
Yeah, not actually cucumber.
They're pickle.

13:14.961 --> 13:16.379
But it was either that
or zucchini.

13:16.379 --> 13:18.131
No.

13:18.131 --> 13:20.300
I have a trigonometry test
tomorrow, and I just found out

13:20.300 --> 13:22.385
there's an after‐hours
study group at the school.

13:22.385 --> 13:24.137
But it's
our tennis tournament.
I know.

13:24.137 --> 13:27.473
But the test is worth,
like, 20% of my grade.

13:27.473 --> 13:28.850
Which is a lot, right?

13:28.850 --> 13:30.059
I think. I don't know.

13:30.059 --> 13:32.520
Aah! I really need
this study group!

13:32.520 --> 13:35.815
All right, love.
I mean, schoolwork comes first.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.317
You fancy more...?
Mnh.

13:38.735 --> 13:40.945
<i>You have arrived</i>
<i>at your destination.</i>

13:40.945 --> 13:43.990
Oh, no. Don't even try
to pretend that thing has GPS.

13:43.990 --> 13:45.700
<i>That's your phone.</i>

13:47.702 --> 13:49.537
Oh. Forgot
to turn my Waze off.

13:49.537 --> 13:50.538
[ Laughs ]

13:50.538 --> 13:51.956
<i>[ Wah‐wah‐wah‐wah! ]</i>

13:51.956 --> 13:54.584
Shut it, JJ.

13:54.584 --> 13:55.543
[ Door closes ]

13:55.543 --> 13:57.253
Can't those two
just make up?

13:57.253 --> 14:00.882
Aw, sometimes you just have to
let your teenage son

14:00.882 --> 14:03.634
and his adult friend
work it out on their own.

14:03.634 --> 14:04.802
I'm sick of this.

14:04.802 --> 14:06.304
I'm getting them
back together.

14:06.304 --> 14:07.346
[ Scoffs ] How?

14:07.346 --> 14:08.890
Have you ever seen
a little movie

14:08.890 --> 14:11.559
called "The Parent Trap"?

14:11.559 --> 14:13.144
<i>Honey, what are you doing</i>
<i>in those clothes?</i>

14:13.144 --> 14:14.395
<i>We've got</i>
<i>a plane to catch.</i>

14:14.395 --> 14:16.689
<i>Here's the deal, Mom ‐‐</i>
<i>We thought it over,</i>

14:16.689 --> 14:18.524
<i>and we decided</i>
<i>we were being totally...</i>

14:18.524 --> 14:19.984
So, you just want us
to sit here

14:19.984 --> 14:21.486
and watch "The Parent Trap"
with you?

14:21.486 --> 14:23.780
Yeah. I mean, if those two
could get back together,

14:23.780 --> 14:25.114
why can't <i>you?</i>

14:25.114 --> 14:26.240
<i>This is dumb.</i>

14:26.240 --> 14:28.868
That's one thing
we can agree on!

14:28.868 --> 14:30.036
[ Sighs ]

14:31.829 --> 14:33.081
We keep getting left alone
together.

14:33.081 --> 14:34.582
It doesn't get less weird.

14:34.582 --> 14:35.458
Nope.

14:35.458 --> 14:37.460
♪♪

14:38.878 --> 14:40.379
Hello.

14:40.379 --> 14:43.132
Dropping off a study snack
for Ray DiMeo.

14:43.132 --> 14:44.717
Ray? [ Chuckles ]
Ray doesn't need to be here.

14:44.717 --> 14:45.718
He's smart.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.095
Oh, but he said ‐‐

14:47.095 --> 14:51.390
♪♪

14:51.390 --> 14:53.309
I'm smart.

14:53.309 --> 14:55.978
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:59.732 --> 15:01.109
Yes!
Nice!

15:01.109 --> 15:03.111
Yes! Good job.

15:06.280 --> 15:08.241
Wait a second.

15:08.241 --> 15:10.451
This isn't trigonometry.

15:10.451 --> 15:11.911
♪♪

15:14.789 --> 15:16.791
♪♪

15:22.171 --> 15:23.589
Jimmy:
Told you she was excited.

15:23.589 --> 15:25.091
Aaaaaaaaah!

15:26.843 --> 15:29.178
Mom talked to you, huh?

15:29.178 --> 15:30.638
Can you help me
smooth things over?

15:30.638 --> 15:33.891
Smooth things over?
Yeah! Sure!

15:33.891 --> 15:35.017
Yeah?
Totally!

15:35.017 --> 15:36.310
We know how she gets.

15:36.310 --> 15:37.603
We'll handle her.

15:37.603 --> 15:39.856
You have a very weird smile

15:39.856 --> 15:41.858
for someone
who actually wants to help me.

15:41.858 --> 15:42.984
What do you have planned?

15:42.984 --> 15:44.819
Um...

15:44.819 --> 15:46.362
"Sorry. I messed up."

15:46.362 --> 15:48.531
Yeah.
Here's the thing, buddy.

15:48.531 --> 15:51.659
That's a little‐boy apology.

15:51.659 --> 15:54.745
Maybe you spilled some juice
on the couch, Mommy got mad.

15:54.745 --> 15:56.497
This is different.

15:56.497 --> 15:59.208
You're a big boy,
and you made a decision ‐‐

15:59.208 --> 16:01.919
one that you <i>knew</i>
would hurt her.

16:03.838 --> 16:04.797
How do I make it better?

16:04.797 --> 16:05.965
Ah.

16:05.965 --> 16:08.301
That's a big‐boy question.

16:08.301 --> 16:09.886
You didn't think much about
what she wanted before.

16:09.886 --> 16:12.138
Maybe start now.

16:12.138 --> 16:13.764
You'll figure it out.

16:13.764 --> 16:15.683
[ Sighs ] Rich guys.

16:18.769 --> 16:19.770
Kenneth!

16:19.770 --> 16:21.689
JJ wants to talk to you.

16:21.689 --> 16:23.399
Oh.

16:23.399 --> 16:24.483
Out here.

16:24.483 --> 16:25.735
Okay.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.197
<i>Kenneth?</i>

16:29.197 --> 16:30.156
Yes, JJ?

16:30.156 --> 16:31.199
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

16:31.199 --> 16:32.825
<i>I've been a fool.</i>

16:32.825 --> 16:34.535
Really? I can't believe
you're saying that.

16:34.535 --> 16:36.913
<i>Well, believe it.</i>
<i>I'm saying it.</i>

16:36.913 --> 16:40.416
<i>Me, the JJ DiMeo.</i>

16:40.416 --> 16:43.127
<i>Please forgive me</i>
<i>so we can move on.</i>

16:43.127 --> 16:45.755
Well, of course
I forgive you.

16:45.755 --> 16:48.591
It's just...
hard sometimes.

16:48.591 --> 16:50.426
I don't want to treat this
as just a job.

16:50.426 --> 16:52.136
You're my friend.

16:52.136 --> 16:53.721
What's the right balance,
you know?

16:53.721 --> 16:55.765
<i>Yep. Totally.</i>

16:55.765 --> 16:58.643
<i>This has been very annoying</i>
<i>for Dylan.</i>

16:58.643 --> 17:00.311
Well, I know
we'll get there.

17:00.311 --> 17:04.023
Because the important thing is
that we care about each other.

17:04.023 --> 17:06.609
Nothing's gonna change that.

17:06.609 --> 17:07.777
I love you, buddy.

17:10.738 --> 17:12.406
<i>I love you, too.</i>

17:15.243 --> 17:17.787
Well, I'll leave
you guys to it.

17:17.787 --> 17:19.497
♪♪

17:22.208 --> 17:24.961
Hey, what is Mom into?
What does Mom like to do?

17:24.961 --> 17:28.130
I don't know ‐‐
laundry, drive us places,

17:28.130 --> 17:29.131
make appointments.

17:29.131 --> 17:30.883
Other than stuff for us.

17:30.883 --> 17:31.926
Oh.

17:31.926 --> 17:33.636
Reschedule appointments.

17:33.636 --> 17:35.054
[ Groans ]

17:35.054 --> 17:38.391
♪♪

17:38.391 --> 17:41.477
And I thought
<i>you</i> were apologizing.

17:41.477 --> 17:43.521
<i>No, but I heard</i>
<i>what you said.</i>

17:43.521 --> 17:45.731
<i>It makes me think</i>
<i>maybe I should.</i>

17:47.817 --> 17:49.610
<i>I do need you.</i>

17:49.610 --> 17:52.154
<i>And I think</i>
<i>that's what I'm afraid of.</i>

17:52.154 --> 17:55.866
You've got
nothing to worry about.

17:55.866 --> 17:57.159
Need away.

17:57.159 --> 17:58.536
You got me, buddy.

18:01.998 --> 18:03.082
What, you want the board?

18:06.544 --> 18:07.795
There we go.

18:07.795 --> 18:09.880
There.

18:09.880 --> 18:12.174
"This is hard.

18:12.174 --> 18:15.094
Can we go back
to the device?"

18:15.094 --> 18:16.679
Ha ha.
Very funny, JJ.

18:17.847 --> 18:21.100
"You do have a life.

18:21.100 --> 18:25.813
Don't let me
keep you from it."

18:25.813 --> 18:27.523
Yeah, I do,
but that doesn't mean

18:27.523 --> 18:29.317
I want to spend <i>less</i> time
with you.

18:29.317 --> 18:30.568
You're my bro.

18:32.695 --> 18:33.654
Come here.

18:33.654 --> 18:36.866
♪♪

18:36.866 --> 18:38.743
Aaaahh!
Aaaahh!

18:43.539 --> 18:44.749
Fshhh!

18:44.749 --> 18:45.541
Unlock it.

18:45.541 --> 18:46.500
Lock it.

18:46.500 --> 18:47.460
Unlock it.

18:47.460 --> 18:48.586
Right.

18:53.382 --> 18:54.842
[ Breathing heavily ]

18:54.842 --> 18:56.260
[ Imitates explosion ]

18:56.260 --> 18:57.595
You know what?

18:57.595 --> 18:59.472
Maybe we <i>should</i> spend
a little less time together.

18:59.472 --> 19:03.225
♪♪

19:03.225 --> 19:04.685
Mom, I need you
to come with me.

19:04.685 --> 19:06.062
Yeah, not now, Ray.
I'm busy.

19:06.062 --> 19:07.563
It's important.

19:07.563 --> 19:09.565
Look, it's just faster
if you tell me what you need

19:09.565 --> 19:11.484
rather than pretending
you want to hang out with me.

19:11.484 --> 19:12.485
No.

19:12.485 --> 19:13.402
[ Sighs ]

19:14.904 --> 19:16.155
One lump or two?

19:20.242 --> 19:21.452
I thought it'd be nice
to hang out

19:21.452 --> 19:23.329
and do something <i>you</i> like,
for once.

19:25.122 --> 19:27.083
You do like afternoon tea,
right?

19:27.083 --> 19:28.668
I do like
afternoon tea, yes.

19:28.668 --> 19:30.086
I know. I remembered.

19:32.421 --> 19:35.216
One is not completely dressed
for tea

19:35.216 --> 19:37.635
unless one's wearing
a fascinator.

19:40.096 --> 19:41.347
Where'd you learn that?

19:41.347 --> 19:42.765
I Googled it.

19:42.765 --> 19:45.017
Did you also Google
whether they're just for women?

19:47.853 --> 19:48.938
Milk?

19:48.938 --> 19:50.106
Please.

19:53.234 --> 19:56.362
Wow, I really did teach you
how to be a rich little twit,

19:56.362 --> 19:58.239
didn't I?

19:58.239 --> 20:00.157
I don't have a good excuse
for what I did.

20:02.410 --> 20:04.870
I guess I just liked
fitting in with those people.

20:07.164 --> 20:09.125
But this can be
our own little club ‐‐

20:09.125 --> 20:10.543
every bit as fancy
as theirs.

20:10.543 --> 20:11.794
[ Train whistle blares ]

20:11.794 --> 20:14.672
[ Train rumbling ]

20:14.672 --> 20:17.675
I'm sorry, Mom!
I love you!

20:17.675 --> 20:20.219
I feel like the best part
of being at that club

20:20.219 --> 20:21.846
was the time
I spent with you!

20:21.846 --> 20:23.889
Oh, stop it!
You're going to make me cry!

20:23.889 --> 20:25.182
It's true!

20:25.182 --> 20:27.059
[ Rumbling fades ]

20:27.059 --> 20:28.769
Darling.

20:28.769 --> 20:31.355
I love you, Ray.

20:31.355 --> 20:33.566
If it's important to you,
then one day,

20:33.566 --> 20:36.318
you will figure out a way
to get back to that club.

20:36.318 --> 20:39.739
[ Train whistle blows,
train rumbling ]

20:39.739 --> 20:41.782
Do you think it's safe
for there to be another train

20:41.782 --> 20:42.992
quite so soon?!

20:42.992 --> 20:45.411
It's a tragedy
waiting to happen!

20:45.411 --> 20:46.495
Top up, love?!

20:46.495 --> 20:48.080
Don't mind if I do!

20:52.918 --> 20:55.421
Little stingy on the cucumber
slices there, cabana boy.

20:57.548 --> 21:01.260
"This place
has gone to hell."

21:01.260 --> 21:03.387
You guys aren't gonna
show up all of the time
for free stuff, right?

21:03.387 --> 21:05.431
I'd rather not say.

21:05.431 --> 21:07.641
Okeydoke.

21:07.641 --> 21:09.226
Today is my last day.

21:09.226 --> 21:10.644
Dylan: Cabana boy!

21:14.231 --> 21:15.566
Ka‐pow!

21:15.566 --> 21:17.193
♪♪

21:17.193 --> 21:18.652
I'll be leaving now.

21:18.652 --> 21:20.154
Thank you.
